lle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Sixth Rank|ja|正六位|1=Senior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank|ja|従六位|1=Junior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Seventh Rank|ja|正七位|1=Senior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Eighth Rank|ja|正八位|1=Senior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Eighth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Ninth Rank|ja|正九位|1=Senior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Ninth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Ninth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Ninth Rank|ja|従九位|1=Junior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Ninth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Ninth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Greater Initial Rank|ja|大初位|1=Greater Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Lesser Initial Rank|ja|少初位|1=Lesser Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lesser Initial Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Lesser Initial Rank|qq=}} endRanklist--><!--Senior Sixth Rank--><!--Senior Sixth Rank--><!--Senior Sixth Rank--><!--Senior Sixth Rank--><!--Senior Sixth Rank--><!--Senior Sixth Rank--><!--Senior Sixth Rank-->

{{Citation needed|date=August 2015}}

'''Shōrokui''' (正六位) is one of the {{ill|Court Ranks in Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ranks of Japan|qq=}} and [[:en:Shinkai (divine rank)|divine Ranks]]. It is positioned below {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位|1=Junior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} and above {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank|ja|従六位|1=Junior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|qq=}}.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-Ranks/court-Ranks/</ref> In terms of decorations, it corresponds to the Fifth Class of {{ill|Orders of Merit|ja|勲等|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Orders of Merit|qq=}} and the Fifth Class of the [[:en:Order of the Golden Kite|Order of the Golden Kite]].

Under the [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryō system]], the Sixth Rank was granted to {{ill|Kaike|ja|介|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaike|qq=}}, who served as the deputy governor of lower provinces. It was classified as a Rank for {{ill|Jige|ja|地下人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jige|qq=}} (non-court nobles) and was distinctly separate from the Fifth Rank or higher, which denoted nobility ({{ill|Tsūki|ja|通貴|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsūki|qq=}}). Those holding the Sixth Rank were not permitted {{ill|Shōden|ja|昇殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōden|qq=}} (entry to the palace). However, [[:en:Kurōdo-dokoro|Kurōdo]] (Chamberlains) were exceptions; their roles allowed them palace access, and those of the Sixth Rank were called {{ill|Rokui Kurōdo|ja|六位蔵人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokui Kurōdo|qq=}}, collectively referred to as {{ill|Tenjōbito|ja|殿上人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenjōbito|qq=}} alongside those of the Fifth Rank or higher.

In terms of [[:en:Shinkai (divine rank)|divine Ranks]], Shōrokui is the lowest Rank. The [[:en:Samurai|Samurai]] originated from the {{ill|Samuraihon|ja|侍品|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Samuraihon|qq=}} class, which consisted of individuals limited to the Sixth Rank who served as bureaucrats and aides to nobles. The Sixth Rank class was also referred to as {{ill|Aosamurai|ja|青侍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aosamurai|qq=}} (Blue Samurai) due to their {{ill|Po (clothing)|lt=Po robe|ja|袍|ja|袍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Po (clothing)|qq=}} being light blue in color.

In the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|2=ja|3=明治|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji period|qq=}} and later, individuals holding Ranks such as [[:en:Major (rank)|Major]] were appointed to this position.

Today, Shōrokui is posthumously conferred to individuals such as {{ill|Keishisei|ja|警視正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keishisei|qq=}} (Senior Police Superintendent) in the {{ill|Japanese police|ja|日本の警察官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese police|qq=}}, {{ill|Shōbōkan|ja|消防監|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōbōkan|qq=}} (Fire Superintendent) in the {{ill|Firefighting personnel|ja|消防吏員|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Firefighting personnel|qq=}}, chairs of {{ill|Municipal councils in Japan|ja|日本の地方議会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Municipal councils in Japan|qq=}} (city, town, and village councils), founders of special institutions and schools, and artists who have made significant contributions in their respective fields.

